subSubSection.paragraph:
Endosomal skeleton
: Axis of filaments cored by small bundles of 4-5 larger styles-mycalostyles and tracts of few smaller styles running parallel to the axis (
Fig. 11 D
). Axis of stem and body with thick multispicular bundles of styles-mycalostyles that appear to consist mainly of the larger size class, with single or a few larger styles projecting on the terminal papillae at right angles to the axis (
Fig. 11 E
), and a thick cortex encrusted with pseudoamphiasters and other microscleres.
